{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":864,"text":"We live in a very complex environment:"},{"time":3187,"text":"complexity and dynamism"},{"time":5091,"text":"and patterns of evidence"},{"time":7154,"text":"from satellite photographs, from videos."},{"time":10039,"text":"You can even see it outside your window."},{"time":13050,"text":"It's endlessly complex, but somehow familiar,"},{"time":16910,"text":"but the patterns kind of repeat,"},{"time":18870,"text":"but they never repeat exactly."},{"time":21360,"text":"It's a huge challenge to understand."},{"time":25487,"text":"The patterns that you see"},{"time":27619,"text":"are there at all of the different scales,"},{"time":31339,"text":"but you can't chop it into one little bit and say,"},{"time":34245,"text":"\"Oh, well let me just make a smaller climate.\""},{"time":36908,"text":"I can't use the normal products of reductionism"},{"time":41120,"text":"to get a smaller and smaller thing that I can study"},{"time":43842,"text":"in a laboratory and say, \"Oh,"},{"time":46150,"text":"now that's something I now understand.\""},{"time":48546,"text":"It's the whole or it's nothing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51913,"text":"The different scales that give you"},{"time":54465,"text":"these kinds of patterns"},{"time":56587,"text":"range over an enormous range of magnitude,"},{"time":60044,"text":"roughly 14 orders of magnitude,"},{"time":62460,"text":"from the small microscopic particles"},{"time":64951,"text":"that seed clouds"},{"time":67327,"text":"to the size of the planet itself,"},{"time":69887,"text":"from 10 to the minus six"},{"time":71163,"text":"to 10 to the eight,"},{"time":72240,"text":"14 orders of spatial magnitude."},{"time":74532,"text":"In time, from milliseconds to millennia,"},{"time":77943,"text":"again around 14 orders of magnitude."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80998,"text":"What does that mean?"},{"time":82385,"text":"Okay, well if you think about how"},{"time":84324,"text":"you can calculate these things,"},{"time":86984,"text":"you can take what you can see,"},{"time":88944,"text":"okay, I'm going to chop it up"},{"time":89970,"text":"into lots of little boxes,"},{"time":91349,"text":"and that's the result of physics, right?"},{"time":93704,"text":"And if I think about a weather model,"},{"time":95429,"text":"that spans about five orders of magnitude,"},{"time":97923,"text":"from the planet to a few kilometers,"},{"time":101050,"text":"and the time scale"},{"time":102588,"text":"from a few minutes to 10 days, maybe a month."},{"time":107000,"text":"We're interested in more than that."},{"time":108395,"text":"We're interested in the climate."},{"time":109700,"text":"That's years, that's millennia,"},{"time":111841,"text":"and we need to go to even smaller scales."},{"time":114414,"text":"The stuff that we can't resolve,"},{"time":116015,"text":"the sub-scale processes,"},{"time":117980,"text":"we need to approximate in some way."},{"time":119960,"text":"That is a huge challenge."},{"time":121722,"text":"Climate models in the 1990s"},{"time":123910,"text":"took an even smaller chunk of that,"},{"time":125880,"text":"only about three orders of magnitude."},{"time":127898,"text":"Climate models in the 2010s,"},{"time":129993,"text":"kind of what we're working with now,"},{"time":131767,"text":"four orders of magnitude."},{"time":134707,"text":"We have 14 to go,"},{"time":137010,"text":"and we're increasing our capability"},{"time":139210,"text":"of simulating those at about"},{"time":141080,"text":"one extra order of magnitude every decade."},{"time":144626,"text":"One extra order of magnitude in space"},{"time":146521,"text":"is 10,000 times more calculations."},{"time":149770,"text":"And we keep adding more things,"},{"time":152150,"text":"more questions to these different models."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154524,"text":"So what does a climate model look like?"},{"time":157257,"text":"This is an old climate model, admittedly,"},{"time":159598,"text":"a punch card, a single line of Fortran code."},{"time":163678,"text":"We no longer use punch cards."},{"time":165656,"text":"We do still use Fortran."},{"time":167897,"text":"New-fangled ideas like C"},{"time":169854,"text":"really haven't had a big impact"},{"time":173089,"text":"on the climate modeling community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175456,"text":"But how do we go about doing it?"},{"time":176856,"text":"How do we go from that complexity that you saw"},{"time":181480,"text":"to a line of code?"},{"time":184010,"text":"We do it one piece at a time."},{"time":185583,"text":"This is a picture of sea ice"},{"time":187461,"text":"taken flying over the Arctic."},{"time":189559,"text":"We can look at all of the different equations"},{"time":191597,"text":"that go into making the ice grow"},{"time":194709,"text":"or melt or change shape."},{"time":196823,"text":"We can look at the fluxes."},{"time":197954,"text":"We can look at the rate at which"},{"time":199906,"text":"snow turns to ice, and we can code that."},{"time":202751,"text":"We can encapsulate that in code."},{"time":205080,"text":"These models are around"},{"time":206306,"text":"a million lines of code at this point,"},{"time":208389,"text":"and growing by tens of thousands of lines of code"},{"time":211859,"text":"every year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213050,"text":"So you can look at that piece,"},{"time":214703,"text":"but you can look at the other pieces too."},{"time":216625,"text":"What happens when you have clouds?"},{"time":218558,"text":"What happens when clouds form,"},{"time":220717,"text":"when they dissipate, when they rain out?"},{"time":222599,"text":"That's another piece."},{"time":224341,"text":"What happens when we have radiation"},{"time":226187,"text":"coming from the sun, going through the atmosphere,"},{"time":228721,"text":"being absorbed and reflected?"},{"time":230647,"text":"We can code each of those\nvery small pieces as well."},{"time":234626,"text":"There are other pieces:"},{"time":236042,"text":"the winds changing the ocean currents."},{"time":239502,"text":"We can talk about the role of vegetation"},{"time":243272,"text":"in transporting water from the soils"},{"time":245601,"text":"back into the atmosphere."},{"time":247570,"text":"And each of these different elements"},{"time":250484,"text":"we can encapsulate and put into a system."},{"time":254108,"text":"Each of those pieces ends up adding to the whole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259256,"text":"And you get something like this."},{"time":261553,"text":"You get a beautiful representation"},{"time":264401,"text":"of what's going on in the climate system,"},{"time":267023,"text":"where each and every one of those"},{"time":270412,"text":"emergent patterns that you can see,"},{"time":273194,"text":"the swirls in the Southern Ocean,"},{"time":275197,"text":"the tropical cyclone in the Gulf of Mexico,"},{"time":277953,"text":"and there's two more that are going to pop up"},{"time":279594,"text":"in the Pacific at any point now,"},{"time":281948,"text":"those rivers of atmospheric water,"},{"time":284661,"text":"all of those are emergent properties"},{"time":287518,"text":"that come from the interactions"},{"time":289642,"text":"of all of those small-scale processes I mentioned."},{"time":293137,"text":"There's no code that says,"},{"time":295042,"text":"\"Do a wiggle in the Southern Ocean.\""},{"time":296899,"text":"There's no code that says, \"Have two"},{"time":299567,"text":"tropical cyclones that spin around each other.\""},{"time":302465,"text":"All of those things are emergent properties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306277,"text":"This is all very good. This is all great."},{"time":308423,"text":"But what we really want to know"},{"time":309693,"text":"is what happens to these emergent properties"},{"time":311642,"text":"when we kick the system?"},{"time":313347,"text":"When something changes, what\nhappens to those properties?"},{"time":316880,"text":"And there's lots of different ways to kick the system."},{"time":319869,"text":"There are wobbles in the Earth's orbit"},{"time":321902,"text":"over hundreds of thousands of years"},{"time":323781,"text":"that change the climate."},{"time":325807,"text":"There are changes in the solar cycles,"},{"time":327943,"text":"every 11 years and longer, that change the climate."},{"time":331048,"text":"Big volcanoes go off and change the climate."},{"time":334622,"text":"Changes in biomass burning, in smoke,"},{"time":337860,"text":"in aerosol particles, all of those things"},{"time":339723,"text":"change the climate."},{"time":341545,"text":"The ozone hole changed the climate."},{"time":345604,"text":"Deforestation changes the climate"},{"time":347821,"text":"by changing the surface properties"},{"time":349747,"text":"and how water is evaporated"},{"time":351737,"text":"and moved around in the system."},{"time":354203,"text":"Contrails change the climate"},{"time":356488,"text":"by creating clouds where there were none before,"},{"time":359355,"text":"and of course greenhouse gases change the system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363953,"text":"Each of these different kicks"},{"time":366974,"text":"provides us with a target"},{"time":369125,"text":"to evaluate whether we understand"},{"time":371960,"text":"something about this system."},{"time":374121,"text":"So we can go to look at"},{"time":376513,"text":"what model skill is."},{"time":379217,"text":"Now I use the word \"skill\" advisedly:"},{"time":381250,"text":"Models are not right or wrong; they're always wrong."},{"time":383661,"text":"They're always approximations."},{"time":385381,"text":"The question you have to ask"},{"time":387275,"text":"is whether a model tells you more information"},{"time":390354,"text":"than you would have had otherwise."},{"time":392279,"text":"If it does, it's skillful."},{"time":395660,"text":"This is the impact of the ozone hole"},{"time":398114,"text":"on sea level pressure, so\nlow pressure, high pressures,"},{"time":400974,"text":"around the southern oceans, around Antarctica."},{"time":403569,"text":"This is observed data."},{"time":405482,"text":"This is modeled data."},{"time":407570,"text":"There's a good match"},{"time":409164,"text":"because we understand the physics"},{"time":411115,"text":"that controls the temperatures in the stratosphere"},{"time":414253,"text":"and what that does to the winds"},{"time":415999,"text":"around the southern oceans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418180,"text":"We can look at other examples."},{"time":419699,"text":"The eruption of Mount Pinatubo in 1991"},{"time":422555,"text":"put an enormous amount of aerosols, small particles,"},{"time":425354,"text":"into the stratosphere."},{"time":426941,"text":"That changed the radiation\nbalance of the whole planet."},{"time":430088,"text":"There was less energy coming\nin than there was before,"},{"time":432870,"text":"so that cooled the planet,"},{"time":434528,"text":"and those red lines and those green lines,"},{"time":436547,"text":"those are the differences between what we expected"},{"time":439112,"text":"and what actually happened."},{"time":440800,"text":"The models are skillful,"},{"time":442583,"text":"not just in the global mean,"},{"time":444276,"text":"but also in the regional patterns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447320,"text":"I could go through a dozen more examples:"},{"time":450160,"text":"the skill associated with solar cycles,"},{"time":453010,"text":"changing the ozone in the stratosphere;"},{"time":455080,"text":"the skill associated with orbital changes"},{"time":457427,"text":"over 6,000 years."},{"time":459483,"text":"We can look at that too, and the models are skillful."},{"time":461881,"text":"The models are skillful in response to the ice sheets"},{"time":464975,"text":"20,000 years ago."},{"time":466495,"text":"The models are skillful"},{"time":468166,"text":"when it comes to the 20th-century trends"},{"time":471070,"text":"over the decades."},{"time":472585,"text":"Models are successful at modeling"},{"time":474867,"text":"lake outbursts into the North Atlantic"},{"time":477472,"text":"8,000 years ago."},{"time":479237,"text":"And we can get a good match to the data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483463,"text":"Each of these different targets,"},{"time":485850,"text":"each of these different evaluations,"},{"time":487980,"text":"leads us to add more scope"},{"time":490371,"text":"to these models,"},{"time":491522,"text":"and leads us to more and more"},{"time":494266,"text":"complex situations that we can ask"},{"time":498254,"text":"more and more interesting questions,"},{"time":500823,"text":"like, how does dust from the Sahara,"},{"time":503533,"text":"that you can see in the orange,"},{"time":505267,"text":"interact with tropical cyclones in the Atlantic?"},{"time":508710,"text":"How do organic aerosols from biomass burning,"},{"time":512187,"text":"which you can see in the red dots,"},{"time":514910,"text":"intersect with clouds and rainfall patterns?"},{"time":517844,"text":"How does pollution, which you can see"},{"time":519631,"text":"in the white wisps of sulfate pollution in Europe,"},{"time":523530,"text":"how does that affect the\ntemperatures at the surface"},{"time":526865,"text":"and the sunlight that you get at the surface?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530353,"text":"We can look at this across the world."},{"time":533841,"text":"We can look at the pollution from China."},{"time":537501,"text":"We can look at the impacts of storms"},{"time":541099,"text":"on sea salt particles in the atmosphere."},{"time":544543,"text":"We can see the combination"},{"time":547104,"text":"of all of these different things"},{"time":549275,"text":"happening all at once,"},{"time":550743,"text":"and we can ask much more interesting questions."},{"time":553150,"text":"How do air pollution and climate coexist?"},{"time":557774,"text":"Can we change things"},{"time":559283,"text":"that affect air pollution and\nclimate at the same time?"},{"time":561872,"text":"The answer is yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564216,"text":"So this is a history of the 20th century."},{"time":567260,"text":"The first one is the model."},{"time":569503,"text":"The weather is a little bit different"},{"time":570910,"text":"to what actually happened."},{"time":572199,"text":"The second one are the observations."},{"time":574231,"text":"And we're going through the 1930s."},{"time":576556,"text":"There's variability, there are things going on,"},{"time":579380,"text":"but it's all kind of in the noise."},{"time":581562,"text":"As you get towards the 1970s,"},{"time":584424,"text":"things are going to start to change."},{"time":586433,"text":"They're going to start to look more similar,"},{"time":588495,"text":"and by the time you get to the 2000s,"},{"time":591063,"text":"you're already seeing the\npatterns of global warming,"},{"time":593705,"text":"both in the observations and in the model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596454,"text":"We know what happened over the 20th century."},{"time":598581,"text":"Right? We know that it's gotten warmer."},{"time":600341,"text":"We know where it's gotten warmer."},{"time":601952,"text":"And if you ask the models why did that happen,"},{"time":604692,"text":"and you say, okay, well, yes,"},{"time":606817,"text":"basically it's because of the carbon dioxide"},{"time":608683,"text":"we put into the atmosphere."},{"time":610662,"text":"We have a very good match"},{"time":612344,"text":"up until the present day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614971,"text":"But there's one key reason why we look at models,"},{"time":618391,"text":"and that's because of this phrase here."},{"time":620612,"text":"Because if we had observations of the future,"},{"time":623107,"text":"we obviously would trust them more than models,"},{"time":626436,"text":"But unfortunately,"},{"time":628380,"text":"observations of the future\nare not available at this time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633920,"text":"So when we go out into the\nfuture, there's a difference."},{"time":636625,"text":"The future is unknown, the future is uncertain,"},{"time":639187,"text":"and there are choices."},{"time":641591,"text":"Here are the choices that we have."},{"time":643424,"text":"We can do some work to mitigate"},{"time":645563,"text":"the emissions of carbon dioxide into the atmosphere."},{"time":648358,"text":"That's the top one."},{"time":650284,"text":"We can do more work"},{"time":652190,"text":"to really bring it down"},{"time":654366,"text":"so that by the end of the century,"},{"time":656584,"text":"it's not much more than there is now."},{"time":659048,"text":"Or we can just leave it to fate"},{"time":662815,"text":"and continue on"},{"time":664308,"text":"with a business-as-usual type of attitude."},{"time":668054,"text":"The differences between these choices"},{"time":671510,"text":"can't be answered by looking at models."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676307,"text":"There's a great phrase"},{"time":677946,"text":"that Sherwood Rowland,"},{"time":679739,"text":"who won the Nobel Prize for the chemistry"},{"time":683603,"text":"that led to ozone depletion,"},{"time":685876,"text":"when he was accepting his Nobel Prize,"},{"time":688273,"text":"he asked this question:"},{"time":689652,"text":"\"What is the use of having developed a science"},{"time":691963,"text":"well enough to make predictions if, in the end,"},{"time":695224,"text":"all we're willing to do is stand around"},{"time":698053,"text":"and wait for them to come true?\""},{"time":700760,"text":"The models are skillful,"},{"time":703497,"text":"but what we do with the\ninformation from those models"},{"time":706815,"text":"is totally up to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708986,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710924,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}